---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'What Is AI Agent Memory?',
  description: 'AI agent memory gives coding assistants persistent context across sessions. Learn how observation capture, hybrid search, and context injection eliminate amnesia in AI-powered development.',
  url: 'https://telepathine.ai/what-is-ai-agent-memory',
  author: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'ELiA',
  },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'ELiA',
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What Is AI Agent Memory?"
  description="AI agent memory gives coding assistants persistent context across sessions. Learn how observation capture, hybrid search, and context injection work — and why your agent needs them."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  canonicalUrl="https://telepathine.ai/what-is-ai-agent-memory"
>
  <section class="content-layer px-4 pb-8 pt-24 sm:px-6 sm:pt-32 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Guide</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2">What Is AI Agent Memory?</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg" style="color: var(--text-muted);">AI agent memory is a persistent storage layer that lets coding assistants remember decisions, changes, and learnings across sessions — so they never start from zero.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-layer section-divider px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8">
      <div>
        <h2>The problem: stateless agents</h2>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Most AI coding assistants are stateless. When you close a session, the context disappears. Next time you open the same project, you re-explain your architecture, your conventions, your trade-offs. Every. Single. Time.</p>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">This isn't just annoying — it's expensive. Context window tokens cost money. Repeated explanations waste compute. And worse, your agent can't build on its own prior work because it doesn't remember doing it.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>What AI agent memory does</h2>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">An AI agent memory system captures, stores, and retrieves context for your coding agents. It works in three stages:</p>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="step-circle">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">Capture</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Record decisions, code changes, learnings, and tool interactions as structured observations. Each observation gets a type, title, narrative, extracted facts, and key concepts — enriched automatically.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="step-circle">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">Search</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Hybrid search combines full-text keyword matching with semantic vector similarity. Find what you need by exact term or by meaning — scoped to your project, not someone else's.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="step-circle">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">Inject</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Progressive context injection delivers formatted, compressed context to your agent at session start. Header, timeline, summary, footer — your agent sees what it needs, not a data dump.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Without persistent memory, your AI assistant treats every session as a blank slate. With it, your agent accumulates institutional knowledge — learning your project's patterns, recording your decisions, and surfacing relevant context precisely when needed.</p>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">The result: less repetition, faster onboarding, more consistent output, and fewer hallucinations from missing context.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>How Telepathine.ai does it</h2>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Telepathine.ai is the portable memory layer for AI agents. It's engine-agnostic (works with Claude, Cursor, Gemini, Windsurf, Copilot, and any MCP-compatible client), project-scoped (your data stays in your project), and MCP-native (16 tools via the Model Context Protocol).</p>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--text-muted);">The Morpheus pipeline processes raw observations into structured, searchable knowledge — normalizing, deduplicating, superseding stale entries, applying decay, and generating session summaries automatically.</p>
        <pre class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto rounded-lg p-4 text-sm" style="background: var(--bg-code); border: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--text-copy);"><code>{`# Session 1 — your agent works and records
curl -X POST https://api.telepathine.ai/v1/sessions \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TELEPATHINE_API_KEY" \\
  -d '{"project":"my-app"}'

# Session 2 — new session, old context surfaces
curl https://api.telepathine.ai/v1/context/inject?projects=my-app \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TELEPATHINE_API_KEY"

# Agent sees prior decisions, changes, and summaries
# without you re-explaining anything`}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Key concepts</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4">
          <div class="surface-card p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">Observation</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">A single recorded memory — a decision, change, learning, or tool interaction. Structured with type, title, narrative, facts, and concepts.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">Session</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">A time-bounded interaction between your agent and your project. Sessions track lifecycle: start, observe, summarize, complete.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">Context Injection</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">The formatted, compressed context delivered to your agent at session start. Progressive disclosure: timeline, summary, key facts.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-4">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">Morpheus Pipeline</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">The observation intelligence layer: normalize, deduplicate, supersede, decay, consolidate, and summarize raw data into structured knowledge.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="surface-panel p-6 text-center">
        <h3>Start giving your agent memory</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">10,000 observations free per month. No credit card required.</p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="/docs/quickstart" class="btn-accent">Quick Start Guide →</a>
          <a href="/features" class="btn-ghost">See All Features</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
